<subSubSection pageId="141" pageNumber="901" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="141.[669,1340,2504,2931]" pageId="141" pageNumber="901">
Phylogenetic position of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1914" box="[1106,1208,2584,2617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="141" pageNumber="901" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flora">K. flora</taxonomicName>
is uncertain because it has not been included in any genetic studies. Specimens previously identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1914" box="[940,1045,2702,2735]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="141" pageNumber="901" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="flora">K. flora</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1142,1259,2702,2735]" name="Vietnam" pageId="141" pageNumber="901">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
have recently been described as a new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[748,871,2781,2814]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Kerivoula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="141" pageNumber="901" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="titania">K. titania</taxonomicName>
. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="141" pageNumber="901" type="distribution">
